com.koloboke.function

Interface ObjByteConsumer<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the first argument to the operation

    public interface ObjByteConsumer<T>
    Represents an operation that accepts an object-valued and a byte-valued argument, and returns no result. This is the (reference, byte) specialization of BiConsumer. Unlike most other functional interfaces, ObjByteConsumer is expected to operate via side-effects.
    See Also:
    BiConsumer
